---
import imgNNF2024 from '~/assets/images/call-to-action/andrew_agbaje_NNF_Award_2024.webp';
import imgNNF2025 from '~/assets/images/call-to-action/andrew_agbaje_NNF_Award_2025.webp';
import imgTedxVaasa from '~/assets/images/index/tedx-vaasa-prof-andrew-agbaje-urfit-child-presentation.webp';
import imgNovoNordisk from '~/assets/images/index/urfit-child_novo_nordisk_foundation.webp';
import imgResearchVisualization from '~/assets/images/index/urfit-child-prevention-stages-visualization.webp';
import CustomVimeo from '~/components/common/CustomVimeo.astro';
import CallToActionWidget from '~/components/widgets/CallToAction.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Steps from '~/components/widgets/Steps.astro';
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { getPermalink } from '~/utils/permalinks';
import { YouTube } from 'astro-embed';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Research-Based Health Guidelines for Children | Call to Action',
  description:
    "Discover evidence-based recommendations for children's health assessment. Learn why traditional BMI measurements should be complemented with waist-to-height ratio for accurate diagnosis.",
  ignoreTitleTemplate: true,
  openGraph: {
    title: 'Research-Based Health Guidelines for Children | Call to Action',
    description:
      "Discover evidence-based recommendations for children's health assessment. Learn why traditional BMI measurements should be complemented with waist-to-height ratio for accurate diagnosis.",
    type: 'website',
    image: imgResearchVisualization,
    article: {
      publishedTime: '2025-01-17T05:06:01+02:00',
      modifiedTime: '2025-01-17T05:06:01+02:00',
      authors: ['urFIT-child Research Group'],
      tags: ['children health', 'health guidelines', 'obesity diagnosis', 'waist-to-height ratio', 'BMI limitations'],
    },
  },
  twitter: {
    handle: '@urFIT-child',
    site: '@urFIT-child',
    cardType: 'summary_large_image',
  },
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <Steps
    tagline="Call to Action"
    classes={{ container: 'pb-0 md:pb-0 lg:pb-0' }}
    title="We aim to translate research findings into clinical and public health practice. Below are a few recommendations based on our research."
    items={[
      {
        title: `1. Beyond BMI: <span class="font-medium"><a class="text-blue-600 hover:underline" href={${getPermalink('/waist-height-calculator')}}>Use waist to height ratio calculator </a> for accurate diagnosis</span>`,
        description:
          'Please do not diagnose overweight and obesity in children and adolescents with body mass index (BMI) alone. BMI was NEVER designed to detect obesity in an individual. Kindly use the waist to height ratio calculator to confirm if the body size is due to fat mass or if the children are simply heavy due to muscle mass.',
        icon: 'tabler:ruler-measure',
      },
      {
        title: '2. Rethinking labels: <span class="font-medium">Focus on fat, not weight</span>',
        description:
          'It is stigmatizing to describe a child as overweight or obese. Children are not bags of salt to be tossed on a weighing scale. Obesity is a problem of excess fat or sick fat (adiposopathy) and not weight, therefore the name of the disease should reflect such. Being overweight should now be termed adiposopathy grade 1 and obesity as adiposopathy grade 2.',
        icon: 'tabler:scale-off',
      },
      {
        title: '3. Keep moving: <span class="font-medium">Light daily exercise for a healthier future</span>',
        description:
          'Sedentary time above 6 hours/day from childhood prematurely damages the heart, arteries, and liver, and increases cholesterol, blood pressure, glucose, inflammation, and fat mass levels by mid-twenties.  The optimal solution is engaging in light exercises of at least 3 hours every day. Examples of light exercises are long walks, house chores, slow dancing, slow swimming, and slow bicycling.',
        icon: 'tabler:bike',
      },
      {
        title: '4. Protect young hearts: <span class="font-medium">Say no to tobacco</span>',
        description:
          'Smoking tobacco from childhood damages the heart structure and functions prematurely by young adulthood. Age 13 to 17 years is the most critical time for adopting smoking habits as the increase in smoking prevalence rises fifteen times within this 4-year gap. Unfortunately, 6 out of 10 children and teenagers who initiate the use of nicotine products will continue smoking for several decades. Parents must lead by example, no smoking at home, please.',
        icon: 'tabler:smoking-no',
      },
      {
        title:
          '5. Get active: <span class="font-medium">MVPA keeps kids smoke-free, light exercise keeps them healthy</span>',
        description:
          'Engaging in moderate-to-vigorous physical activity (MVPA) in childhood may significantly prevent sixty percent of children from initiating a tobacco smoking habit. Importantly, MVPA effect is very strong in preventing and reducing smoking but its effect on decreasing elevated cholesterol, insulin resistance, fat, inflammation, and blood pressure is significantly weaker than light exercise.',
        icon: 'tabler:run',
      },
      {
        title: '6. Early checks matter: <span class="font-medium">Monitor cholesterol to protect young hearts</span>',
        description:
          "Elevated cholesterol level in adolescence is a risk factor for premature heart damage. Parents and caregivers should kindly check children and adolescents' cholesterol levels at least once every ten years even if there is no family history of high cholesterol levels. Waiting until age 40 years to check oneâ€™s cholesterol level for the first time is too late given the risk of an already established heart disease.",
        icon: 'tabler:shield-check',
      },
      {
        title:
          '7. Healthy habits: <span class="font-medium">Regular home blood pressure checks for a happy future</span>',
        description:
          "Home blood pressure monitoring could be extended to adolescents and may be checked once in six months. Family participation in blood pressure checks at home is highly encouraged. We have shown that elevated blood pressure is risky for young adults' hearts. We wish kids globally a healthy, happy, and enjoyable life.",
        icon: 'tabler:heartbeat',
      },
      {
        title: 'Ready!',
        icon: 'tabler:check',
      },
    ]}
  />

  <!-- Hero Widget ******************* -->

  <Hero
    image={{
      src: imgResearchVisualization,
      alt: 'urFIT-child research visualization',
    }}
  />

  <!-- TEDx Vaasa 2025 Section *********** -->

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 xl:py-[80px] bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-800">
    <div class="max-w-3xl xl:max-w-[768px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 xl:px-[24px]">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl md:text-4xl xl:text-[36px] xl:leading-[40px] font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 xl:mb-[16px]"
        >
          TEDx Vaasa 2025
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl xl:text-[20px] xl:leading-[28px] text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mx-auto">
          Prof. Andrew Agbaje presents groundbreaking research on childhood health and obesity prevention at TEDx Vaasa
          2025.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="w-full">
          <YouTube
            id="Zr-EHkDEAmo"
            class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full"
            poster={imgTedxVaasa.src}
            title="TEDx Vaasa 2025 - Prof. Andrew Agbaje"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ASN-NNF Award 2025 Section *********** -->

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 xl:py-[80px]">
    <div class="max-w-3xl xl:max-w-[768px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 xl:px-[24px]">
      <div class="text-center mb-12 xl:mb-[48px]">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl md:text-4xl xl:text-[36px] xl:leading-[40px] font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 xl:mb-[16px]"
        >
          ASN-NNF Award 2025
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl xl:text-[20px] xl:leading-[28px] text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Prof. Andrew Agbaje receives the prestigious American Society of Nutrition Foundation-Novo Nordisk Foundation
          2025 Flemming Quaade Award for Innovative Approaches to Childhood Obesity.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="w-full">
          <YouTube
            id="EQDC2E6R4xM"
            class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full"
            poster={imgNovoNordisk.src}
            title="ASN-NNF Award 2025 - Prof. Andrew Agbaje"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EASO-NNF Award 2024 Section *********** -->

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 xl:py-[80px] bg-gray-50 dark:bg-slate-800">
    <div class="max-w-3xl xl:max-w-[768px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 xl:px-[24px]">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2
          class="text-3xl md:text-4xl xl:text-[36px] xl:leading-[40px] font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4 xl:mb-[16px]"
        >
          EASO-NNF Award 2024
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl xl:text-[20px] xl:leading-[28px] text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Prof. Andrew Agbaje discusses winning the European Association for the Study of Obesity-Novo Nordisk
          Foundation Award for Child Obesity research.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8 xl:space-y-[32px]">
        <!-- First Vimeo Video -->
        <div class="w-full">
          <CustomVimeo id="944938770/8269ce30e4" class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full" poster={imgNNF2024} />
        </div>

        <!-- Second Vimeo Video -->
        <div class="w-full">
          <CustomVimeo id="1080620838/33801202a5" class="rounded-lg shadow-lg w-full" poster={imgNNF2025} />
        </div>

        <!-- EASO Website Link -->
        <div class="text-center mt-6 xl:mt-[24px]">
          <a
            href="https://easo.org/watch-andrew-agbaje-discuss-winning-the-easo-nn-foundation-award-for-child-obesity/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 xl:px-[24px] xl:py-[12px] bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold rounded-lg transition-colors duration-200"
          >
            <svg
              class="w-5 h-5 mr-2 xl:w-[20px] xl:h-[20px] xl:mr-[8px]"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14"></path>
            </svg>
            Watch on EASO Website
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CallToAction Widget *********** -->

  <CallToActionWidget
    title="Our waist to height ratio calculator WHtR"
    subtitle="Waist to height ratio calculator WHtR 2025 based on 30 years of WHtR data. Discover normal waist to height ratio and healthy waist to height ratio values."
    actions={[
      {
        variant: 'primary',
        target: '_self',
        text: 'Try the waist to height ratio calculator',
        href: getPermalink('/waist-height-calculator'),
        icon: 'tabler:calculator',
      },
    ]}
  />
</Layout>
